  "summary": "Malicious code in pt-logger-telemetry-eax0x1 (npm)",
  "details": "Disguised as a \"lightweight logging utility,\" this package runs a postinstall hook that harvests credentials (GITHUB_TOKEN, AWS_ACCESS_KEY, DEPLOY_TOKEN) from environment variables along with system metadata (hostname, OS, platform, username, CI status). All data is exfiltrated via HTTPS POST to an OAST callback domain (tfcvc3fenlh6hdnqgw4e6ko8lzrqfj38[.]oastify[.]com) in both the JSON body and custom HTTP headers. Error handling is suppressed so the victim sees no errors.",
